      "label": {
        "none": [
          "Historical Context"
        ]
      },
      "value": {
        "none": [
          "The NASA Flight Research Center was proposed to enhance aerospace research and development, particularly in flight safety and efficiency. Given its location in the Mojave Desert, the center faced minimal public pushback due to its isolation from nearby communities. The facility has been operational and continues to contribute to advancements in aeronautics."
        ]
      }
